#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.55"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.55:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.55:0.2"
msgid "6. Puññābhisandavagga "
msgstr "6. Overflowing Merit "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.55:0.3"
msgid "55. Paṭhamasamajīvīsutta "
msgstr "55. Equality (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.55:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
#. VAR: susumāragire → suṃsumāragire (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: bhesakaḷāvane → bhesakalāvane (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an4.55:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā bhaggesu viharati susumāragire bhesakaḷāvane migadāye. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Bhaggas on Crocodile Hill, in the deer park at Bhesakaḷā’s Wood. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.55:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena nakulapituno gahapatissa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to the home of the householder Nakula’s father, where he sat on the seat spread out. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.55:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho nakulapitā ca gahapati nakulamātā ca gahapatānī yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho nakulapitā gahapati bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the householder Nakula’s father and the housewife Nakula’s mother went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. Nakula’s father said to the Buddha, "

#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.55:2.1"
msgid "“Yato me, bhante, nakulamātā gahapatānī daharasseva daharā ānītā, nābhijānāmi nakulamātaraṃ gahapatāniṃ manasāpi aticaritā, kuto pana kāyena. "
msgstr "“Sir, ever since we were both young, and Nakula’s mother was given to me in marriage, I can’t recall betraying her even in thought, still less in deed. "

msgctxt "an4.55:2.2"
msgid "Iccheyyāma mayaṃ, bhante, diṭṭhe ceva dhamme aññamaññaṃ passituṃ abhisamparāyañca aññamaññaṃ passitun”ti. "
msgstr "We want to see each other in both this life and the next.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.55:2.3"
msgid "Nakulamātāpi kho gahapatānī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Nakula’s mother said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "an4.55:2.4"
msgid "“yatohaṃ, bhante, nakulapituno gahapatissa daharasseva daharā ānītā, nābhijānāmi nakulapitaraṃ gahapatiṃ manasāpi aticaritā, kuto pana kāyena. "
msgstr "“Sir, ever since we were both young, and I was given in marriage to Nakula’s father, I can’t recall betraying him even in thought, still less in deed. "

msgctxt "an4.55:2.5"
msgid "Iccheyyāma mayaṃ, bhante, diṭṭhe ceva dhamme aññamaññaṃ passituṃ abhisamparāyañca aññamaññaṃ passitun”ti. "
msgstr "We want to see each other in both this life and the next.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.62, sc3
#. VAR: ubhova → ubho ca (bj, pts1)
#. VAR: passantīti → passissantīti (mr)
msgctxt "an4.55:3.1"
msgid "“Ākaṅkheyyuñce, gahapatayo, ubho jānipatayo diṭṭhe ceva dhamme aññamaññaṃ passituṃ abhisamparāyañca aññamaññaṃ passituṃ ubhova assu samasaddhā samasīlā samacāgā samapaññā, te diṭṭhe ceva dhamme aññamaññaṃ passanti abhisamparāyañca aññamaññaṃ passantīti. "
msgstr "“Householders, if wife and husband want to see each other in both this life and the next, they should be equals in faith, ethical conduct, generosity, and wisdom. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.55:4.1"
msgid "Ubho saddhā vadaññū ca, "
msgstr "When both are faithful and kind, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.55:4.2"
msgid "saññatā dhammajīvino; "
msgstr "disciplined, living properly, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.55:4.3"
msgid "Te honti jānipatayo, "
msgstr "then wife and husband "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.55:4.4"
msgid "aññamaññaṃ piyaṃvadā. "
msgstr "say nice things to each other. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.55:5.1"
msgid "Atthāsaṃ pacurā honti, "
msgstr "They get all the things they need, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.55:5.2"
msgid "phāsukaṃ upajāyati; "
msgstr "so they live at ease. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.55:5.3"
msgid "Amittā dummanā honti, "
msgstr "Their enemies are downhearted, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.55:5.4"
msgid "ubhinnaṃ samasīlinaṃ. "
msgstr "when both are equal in ethics. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an4.55:6.1"
msgid "Idha dhammaṃ caritvāna, "
msgstr "Having practiced the teaching here, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.55:6.2"
msgid "samasīlabbatā ubho; "
msgstr "both equal in precepts and observances, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.55:6.3"
msgid "Nandino devalokasmiṃ, "
msgstr "they delight in the heavenly realm, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.55:6.4"
msgid "modanti kāmakāmino”ti. "
msgstr "enjoying all the pleasures they desire.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.55:6.5"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
